# Local-only Worker secrets for `wrangler dev`. Copy to `.dev.vars` (gitignored)
# and fill in. In production set these with `wrangler secret put <NAME>`.

# Better Auth signing secret. Generate one: `openssl rand -base64 32`
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=replace-me

# Optional: pin the OAuth issuer the MCP discovery metadata advertises (ADR
# 0026). Needed to test the MCP OAuth flow against `wrangler dev` — without it
# the dev proxy's custom-domain simulation makes the inferred origin the prod
# domain. In prod set the real origin via BETTER_AUTH_URL.
# BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:8787

# Optional companion to the above: the same custom-domain simulation also
# rewrites the request Origin header to the prod domain, so Better Auth's CSRF
# check rejects local sign-in unless that origin is trusted. Set this to make
# the OAuth login flow work under `wrangler dev`. Local-only; in prod the origin
# IS the prod domain and is already trusted via BETTER_AUTH_URL.
# BETTER_AUTH_TRUSTED_ORIGINS=http://app.dotflowy.com,https://app.dotflowy.com

# Optional: extra CSP `frame-ancestors` sources allowed to embed the anonymous
# landing demo (`?demo=1`) — needed to test the landing hero iframe against
# `wrangler dev` (the landing dev server runs on :3100). Space-separated CSP
# host sources. Never set in prod: there, only https://dotflowy.com may frame
# the demo, and the authenticated app is never framable cross-origin at all.
# DEMO_FRAME_ANCESTORS=http://localhost:3100
